---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import PageHero from "../../components/PageHero.astro";
import CtaBand from "../../components/CtaBand.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="SYAG Security & Architecture — Cloud-Native, Isolated, Compliant"
  description="SYAG is hosted on Microsoft Azure with schema-per-tenant data isolation, end-to-end encryption, role-based access control, and a compliance path for Saudi NCA and UAE IA requirements."
>
  <PageHero
    label="Architecture & Security"
    headline="Built <span style='color:#4ade80'>secure</span>. Built to <span style='color:#35E0FF'>comply</span>."
    subheadline="SYAG is designed with security at every layer — from how your data is stored to how your users authenticate to how your facility's information is isolated from every other tenant on the platform."
  />

  <!-- INFRASTRUCTURE -->
  <section class="space-y-6">
    <h2 class="quartr-heading text-3xl font-semibold text-white">Hosted on Microsoft Azure</h2>
    <div class="glass-card space-y-4">
      <p class="text-sm text-white/60">
        SYAG runs on Microsoft Azure infrastructure, providing enterprise-grade reliability, global
        availability, and regional data residency options critical for MEA compliance requirements.
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-white/60">
        <li><strong class="text-white/80">Hosting:</strong> Azure App Service (managed, auto-scaling)</li>
        <li><strong class="text-white/80">Database:</strong> Azure-hosted PostgreSQL with automated backups</li>
        <li><strong class="text-white/80">CDN & WAF:</strong> Azure Front Door with Web Application Firewall</li>
        <li><strong class="text-white/80">Messaging:</strong> Azure Service Bus for reliable event delivery</li>
        <li><strong class="text-white/80">IoT:</strong> Azure IoT Hub (S1 Standard) for device connectivity</li>
        <li><strong class="text-white/80">Uptime SLA:</strong> 99.9% availability</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- DATA ISOLATION -->
  <section class="space-y-6">
    <h2 class="quartr-heading text-3xl font-semibold text-white">Your data stays yours — <span style="color:#4ade80">always</span></h2>
    <div class="glass-card space-y-4">
      <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-white">Schema-per-tenant architecture</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-white/60">
        Every facility on SYAG gets its own isolated PostgreSQL schema. This means your guard records,
        incident logs, visitor data, and asset registry are stored in a completely separate namespace
        from every other customer. No shared tables. No cross-tenant data access. No risk of data
        leakage between facilities.
      </p>
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-white/40">What this means in practice</p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-white/60">
        <li>Your facility admin cannot see another facility's data</li>
        <li>Even if two facilities are in the same city, their data never intersects</li>
        <li>You can request a full export of your data at any time</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- AUTHENTICATION -->
  <section class="space-y-6">
    <h2 class="quartr-heading text-3xl font-semibold text-white">Role-based access. <span style="color:#35E0FF">Zero-trust</span> by design.</h2>
    <div class="glass-card space-y-4">
      <p class="text-sm text-white/60">
        SYAG uses OpenIddict as its identity provider, implementing industry-standard OAuth 2.0 and
        OpenID Connect flows:
      </p>
      <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-white/10">
        <table class="w-full text-left text-sm text-white/70">
          <thead class="bg-white/5 text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-white/50">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3">User type</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3">Auth flow</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3">Session</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-white/10">
            {[
              ["Web admin / supervisor", "Authorization Code + PKCE", "Short-lived JWT + refresh token"],
              ["Guard (mobile app)", "Device Code flow", "Refresh token rotation"],
              ["API integrations", "Client Credentials", "Scoped access tokens"],
            ].map(([user, flow, session]) => (
              <tr>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">{user}</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">{flow}</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">{session}</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-white/40">Role hierarchy</p>
      <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-white/60">
        <li><strong class="text-white/80">Guard</strong> — field operations only (patrol, incidents, visitor scan)</li>
        <li><strong class="text-white/80">Supervisor</strong> — site-level management + guard oversight</li>
        <li><strong class="text-white/80">Admin</strong> — full facility configuration + user management</li>
        <li><strong class="text-white/80">Ops Center</strong> — cross-site read access for monitoring</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-sm text-white/60">Every action is logged with user identity, timestamp, and IP address. Full audit trail, always.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ENCRYPTION -->
  <section class="space-y-6">
    <h2 class="quartr-heading text-3xl font-semibold text-white">Encrypted in <span style="color:#35E0FF">transit</span>. Protected at <span style="color:#4ade80">rest</span>.</h2>
    <div class="glass-card space-y-3">
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-white/60">
        <li>All data transmitted over TLS 1.3</li>
        <li>Database encrypted at rest (AES-256)</li>
        <li>Redis cache data encrypted</li>
        <li>Azure Service Bus messages encrypted in transit</li>
        <li>Passwords hashed using bcrypt with salt</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- COMPLIANCE -->
  <section class="space-y-6">
    <h2 class="quartr-heading text-3xl font-semibold text-white">Compliance-ready for the <span style="color:#ff8a3c">MEA region</span></h2>
    <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
      <div class="glass-card space-y-3">
        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-white">Saudi NCA compliance path</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-white/60">
          For customers requiring alignment with Saudi Arabia's National Cybersecurity Authority (NCA)
          Essential Cybersecurity Controls, SYAG offers an upgrade path to Azure Front Door Premium
          with enhanced WAF rules, DDoS protection, and private link connectivity.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="glass-card space-y-3">
        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-white">UAE IA compliance path</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-white/60">
          For UAE customers under the Information Assurance (IA) framework, SYAG can configure data
          residency within UAE North Azure region, providing geographic data sovereignty.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="glass-card space-y-3">
      <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-white">What we're working on</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-white/60">
        <li>ISO 27001 certification (roadmap)</li>
        <li>SOC 2 Type II (roadmap)</li>
        <li>Penetration test reports (available to enterprise customers under NDA)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CtaBand
    headline="Have <span style='color:#ff8a3c'>compliance</span> requirements? Talk to our team."
    body="We'll walk you through the architecture."
    primaryLabel="Contact us →"
    primaryHref="/contact"
  />
</Layout>
